1
00:00:00,540 --> 00:00:01,950
Previously on Medium

2
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:05,880
Gunshots have reportedly been fired
inside the offices of Aerodytech

3
00:00:05,930 --> 00:00:07,410
Has anyone seen Joe Dubois?

4
00:00:10,490 --> 00:00:11,810
So, are you ready for this?

5
00:00:11,820 --> 00:00:13,180
As ready as I'll ever be.

6
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:14,740
- Welcome back Joe!
- Thank you

7
00:00:15,170 --> 00:00:19,400
Is everything ok at work?

8
00:00:19,410 --> 00:00:20,450
Everything is fine.

9
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,590
Something seems wrong.

10
00:00:21,630 --> 00:00:22,590
<i>Mrs. Dubois,</i>

11
00:00:22,630 --> 00:00:24,590
my name is Marcus Canty.

12
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:25,790
I work with your husband.

13
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:27,150
Since he's come back to work,

14
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,920
<i>he hasn't been attending any meetings,</i>

15
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:30,950
<i>he hasn't been making any phone calls.</i>

16
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,420
<i>Your boss called.</i>

17
00:00:32,460 --> 00:00:34,890
They said they might
want you to see someone.

18
00:00:34,930 --> 00:00:36,320
My name is Cooper Conroy.

19
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:37,490
I'm an attorney,Mr. Dubois.

20
00:00:37,530 --> 00:00:38,720
Can you talk for a moment?

21
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:40,190
Talk about what?

22
00:00:40,230 --> 00:00:43,620
About millions of dollars I
believe you're entitled to.

23
00:00:43,890 --> 00:00:46,820
<i>I dream the same dream every night,</i>

24
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:48,990
and there is nothing
circumstantial about it.

25
00:00:49,030 --> 00:00:50,650
We're going to finish trying this case.

26
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:51,990
We're going to trust the jury.

27
00:00:52,030 --> 00:00:53,320
We find the defendant

28
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:56,650
guilty of murder in the first degree.

29
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,590
Thank you for the encouragement.

30
00:00:58,630 --> 00:01:00,320
I work for the District Attorney,

31
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,650
Manuel Devalos.

32
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:02,820
It's not that exciting.

33
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:04,090
Easy for you to say.

34
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:05,320
You don't sell
pharmaceuticals for a living.

35
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,350
So...

36
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,350
what's it like working for the DA?

37
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:11,220
I thought you needed
to see this. Oh,my God.

38
00:01:11,260 --> 00:01:15,190
It's Natalie Paxton's head
on Ramona Hensley's body.

39
00:01:15,230 --> 00:01:16,720
<i>City Hall is already being inundated</i>

40
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:17,950
with people calling for
the immediate release

41
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,690
of Walter Paxton.

42
00:01:21,130 --> 00:01:22,520
You're expecting a call today...

43
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,790
...or maybe a text?

44
00:01:24,830 --> 00:01:27,190
<i>My husband's kind of
going through something.</i>

45
00:01:27,230 --> 00:01:28,690
Well,now we know where the head

46
00:01:28,730 --> 00:01:30,220
of the third victim ended up.

47
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:31,620
So who's the body belong to?

48
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:34,190
Driver's license photo.

49
00:01:45,210 --> 00:01:46,770
Hey,Dad.

50
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:48,320
Evening,son.

51
00:01:48,330 --> 00:01:49,380
<i>So...</i>

52
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,890
what's all the hubbub?

53
00:01:50,930 --> 00:01:52,390
Huh?

54
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:56,120
What's so important you needed
to raise me from the dead?

55
00:01:56,170 --> 00:01:59,560
Well,I was just kind
of reviewing my options,

56
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:02,590
contemplating my future.

57
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:04,220
Well,you know,I don't get you.

58
00:02:04,270 --> 00:02:05,490
I don't know what you're talking about.

59
00:02:05,530 --> 00:02:06,790
What's to contemplate?

60
00:02:06,830 --> 00:02:09,320
I mean,your future's right here.

61
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:11,090
You got the,the two kids...

62
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:12,790
Three.

63
00:02:12,830 --> 00:02:16,390
...the happy marriage
to Haley Joel Osment.

64
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:19,390
Yeah,I know,I know.

65
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,790
I just...

66
00:02:20,830 --> 00:02:24,290
There were five of us in that room,Dad.

67
00:02:24,330 --> 00:02:27,390
Only two of us made it out alive.

68
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:28,820
Why me?

69
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:30,020
Why not them?

70
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:35,920
Because.

71
00:02:35,970 --> 00:02:37,620
That's it?

72
00:02:37,670 --> 00:02:39,160
That's your answer?

73
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,420
"Because"?

74
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:43,220
You know what your problem is?

75
00:02:43,270 --> 00:02:45,290
You've never been in a war.

76
00:02:45,330 --> 00:02:48,790
My generation... we saw death,

77
00:02:48,830 --> 00:02:51,320
contemplated our own
mortality when we were young

78
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:52,590
so we didn't have to waste

79
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:55,020
the rest of our lives worrying about it.

80
00:02:55,070 --> 00:02:57,590
We realized that death
takes care of itself.

81
00:02:57,630 --> 00:03:01,060
It's life that needs your attention.

82
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,520
Life,huh?

83
00:03:04,930 --> 00:03:07,660
Look,you got a great job.
You got a hot little wife.

84
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:09,990
You got a couple of nice kids,

85
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:13,690
and here you are
wondering why you're alive.

86
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:15,120
You know what you need to do?

87
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:16,290
What's that?

88
00:03:16,330 --> 00:03:18,290
You need to wake up. Oh,really?

89
00:03:18,330 --> 00:03:19,620
I mean it.

90
00:03:19,670 --> 00:03:21,060
Honey,I need you to wake up.

91
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:22,290
Honey? Darling.

92
00:03:22,330 --> 00:03:24,260
Please,just wake up.

93
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,860
Wait a second. No,I'm confused.

94
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:26,860
Why should I?

95
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,990
Give me one good reason.

96
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:34,690
Because I need to talk to
you about a dream I just had.

97
00:03:34,730 --> 00:03:36,920
<i>So they found your friend's body</i>

98
00:03:36,970 --> 00:03:39,590
with the head of the third victim on it?

99
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:42,220
That would make your
friend the fourth victim.

100
00:03:42,270 --> 00:03:43,420
Uh-huh.

101
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:47,760
To be honest,I don't think the
issue is as much who to call

102
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,320
as it is what to say.

103
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:50,560
Well,I have to tell someone.

104
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,920
What are you going to tell them?

105
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:53,360
"I don't know who the next victim is,

106
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,460
but I can tell you about
the one after that"?

107
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,620
<i>It's not as if you know when
any of this is going to happen.</i>

108
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,260
Are you saying I shouldn't tell anybody?

109
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,660
I don't know.

110
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:03,790
Keep in mind this is a dream
you had after two martinis.

111
00:04:03,830 --> 00:04:06,390
Uh... I'm not telling you

112
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:07,520
how to do your job.

113
00:04:07,570 --> 00:04:08,590
I'm just saying that I don't think

114
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,190
there's anyone to call tonight.

115
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:13,920
Right.

116
00:04:13,970 --> 00:04:16,960
Speaking of calling,how's your phone?

117
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,960
Very clean.

118
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,160
Useless,but very clean.

119
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:25,390
Melinda had her baby...

120
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:28,320
and that's who keeps texting me.

121
00:04:28,370 --> 00:04:31,290
She asked about you,by the way.

122
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:32,860
How you're doing.

123
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,420
How you're doing with me.

124
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:38,820
Tell her not very well.

125
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:44,590
But I'm determined to change that.

126
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:47,760
Yeah.

127
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,890
Me,too.

