Dad,where's Mom? Let me switch rooms.

136
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:47,730
Still sleeping,sweetie.

137
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:50,030
Can you give her another one?

138
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,570
Okay,let's see.

139
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:52,570
Here's one.

140
00:05:52,610 --> 00:05:53,600
Jocular.

141
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,930
Hi.

142
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:57,070
What can I do for you,Mr. Conroy?

143
00:05:57,110 --> 00:05:59,000
At the risk of sounding like a cliche?

144
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,000
this call is about
what I can do for you.

145
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:04,900
I thought we left it that you
were going to wait for my call.

146
00:06:04,940 --> 00:06:07,270
And I would have,but you didn't call.

147
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:08,670
Usually when I mention

148
00:06:08,710 --> 00:06:10,830
that there's potentially
millions of dollars involved,

149
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:13,470
people at least let me
buy them a cup of coffee.

150
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:16,700
You do drink coffee,don't
you,Mr. Dubois?

151
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,870
You were looking for me?

152
00:06:21,910 --> 00:06:24,100
Yeah,I was.

153
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:26,400
The name P.D. McCall ring a bell?

154
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,730
I'm sorry?

155
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:28,870
Couple of months ago,

156
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:30,930
you told me about a
reporter from out of town

157
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:33,600
who was calling you,asking
questions about this office,

158
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:36,870
certain particulars about
the Sonny Troyer case.

159
00:06:36,910 --> 00:06:39,430
Do you remember the
name of that reporter?

160
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,970
Not off the top of my head.

161
00:06:41,010 --> 00:06:45,670
I can look it up if it's important.

162
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:50,000
Amid the flood of articles
from around the country

163
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,770
suggesting that,uh,

164
00:06:51,810 --> 00:06:54,130
I completely misjudged this situation,

165
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:56,330
did you happen to see this one?

166
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:58,230
"Aggressive DA's Office

167
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:00,800
Finally Undone by Recapitator. "

168
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:01,800
Undone by what?

169
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:04,200
The Recapitator.

170
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,270
That's what they're calling our killer.

171
00:07:06,310 --> 00:07:08,300
He doesn't just decapitate these women,

172
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:10,370
he re-capitates them,

173
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:11,800
putting the head of his last victim

174
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,500
on the body of his current one.

175
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:15,770
Clever.

176
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:17,570
Anyway,this P.D. McCall

177
00:07:17,610 --> 00:07:20,230
points out that if I had at
least entertained the deal

178
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:22,300
that Paxton's attorney was shopping,

179
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:24,000
that the judge most
certainly would have suspended

180
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,770
the trial prior to the verdict,

181
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:30,300
and we wouldn't be in
the mess we're in now.

182
00:07:30,340 --> 00:07:32,170
An opinion I know you share.

183
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:36,200
Manny,I never said
that to anyone but you.

184
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,600
Of course not.

185
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:40,130
I just can't figure out

186
00:07:40,180 --> 00:07:44,130
<i>why this national reporter
is coming after my scalp.</i>

187
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:58,000
District Attorney's
Office,Allison Dubois speaking.

188
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,300
Are you that blonde I
saw inhaling martinis

189
00:08:00,340 --> 00:08:02,570
at the hotel bar last night?

190
00:08:02,610 --> 00:08:04,070
Uh,who am I speaking with?

191
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:06,370
It's your drinking buddy,Drinking Buddy.

192
00:08:06,410 --> 00:08:07,730
How you holding up this morning?

193
00:08:07,780 --> 00:08:09,200
I'm surviving.

194
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,600
My husband let me sleep
in a bit,which was nice.

195
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:12,830
It's my boss I'm worried about.

196
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,130
Every two minutes,

197
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:16,130
they bring in another
stack of newspaper articles

198
00:08:16,180 --> 00:08:17,130
about how he bungled

199
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:19,000
the whole Paxton thing.

200
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,570
He looks so defeated.

201
00:08:20,610 --> 00:08:22,400
Let's change the subject.

202
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,500
What are you doing?

203
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,370
I am killing time
before a client meeting.

204
00:08:25,410 --> 00:08:27,070
Why? You want to get another drink?

205
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:29,000
Yes,but I can't.

206
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,030
Actually,I'm glad you called.

207
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,930
I wanted to ask you a question.

208
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,000
Oh,excellent.

209
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:34,630
You ask the questions for a change.

210
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:36,570
How long are you going to be in town?

211
00:08:36,610 --> 00:08:37,770
Why? Hubby jealous?

212
00:08:37,810 --> 00:08:38,770
No,I'm serious.

213
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,470
Last night when I left,

214
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:44,600
I thought about you in
that hotel by yourself.

215
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:47,700
I kind of like the way you look
with your head on your own neck.

216
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,970
You are really sweet
in a deeply twisted way.

217
00:08:52,010 --> 00:08:54,030
I am here for as long as it takes me

218
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,230
to get my work done,but
don't be concerned.

219
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,170
There's thousands of
hotel rooms in Phoenix

220
00:08:58,210 --> 00:08:59,530
and only one Recapitator.

221
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:00,970
Recapitator?

222
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:03,670
Oh,my God,I just heard someone
call him that in the elevator.

223
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,270
I can't believe a civilian like you

224
00:09:05,310 --> 00:09:07,030
is already acting like that's his name.

225
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,100
<i>That is his name and I like it.</i>

226
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,930
I told you
- Court TV junkie.

227
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:12,570
So... give me some dirt.

228
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:14,200
What are the police
saying about the connection

229
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:16,270
between Paxton's wife
and this new victim?

230
00:09:16,310 --> 00:09:17,600
Well,that's what's scary.

231
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,900
There doesn't seem to be a
connection other than the fact

232
00:09:19,940 --> 00:09:23,500
that they were both alone
in expensive hotel rooms.

233
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:25,500
It seems completely random,

234
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:28,730
which is why,as much as
I enjoy having you around,

235
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:30,430
I sure would feel much better

236
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:33,500
if you left town until
we catch this guy.

237
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,870
Or- I don't know-
come stay at my house.

238
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:38,600
You can be the referee
between me and my husband.

239
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:41,870
Sorry,I like my job
and I like room service,

240
00:09:41,910 --> 00:09:44,770
but I'd love to do the cocktail
or the lunch thing again.

241
00:09:44,810 --> 00:09:46,030
Anyway,you know what?

242
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,300
I got to go.

243
00:09:47,340 --> 00:09:49,800
For crying out loud,you
work for politicians,girl.

244
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:52,670
Stop worrying about my neck
and watch out for your own.

245
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:54,100
<i>Sorry to keep you waiting.</i>

246
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:56,270
I had a doctor's appointment.

247
00:09:56,310 --> 00:09:58,700
Company-ordered therapy.

248
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:01,330
Eh,it's pretty standard
in situations like this.

249
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:04,700
Forgive me; situations like what?

250
00:10:04,740 --> 00:10:06,900
I think what I've been
through is fairly unique.

251
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,930
I didn't mean to diminish
the impact it's had

252
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,700
on you or,or your life.

253
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:12,170
That's the reason I'm here.

254
00:10:12,210 --> 00:10:14,930
I've actually had quite a bit
of experience in this area.

255
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:16,970
And what is "this area"?

256
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:20,570
Suing the companies where
the,where the violence occurs?

257
00:10:20,610 --> 00:10:22,100
Aren't they victims in all this,too?

258
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:24,700
I mean,they didn't tell my co-worker

259
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:25,930
to bring a gun to work,

260
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:28,800
much less use it against his colleagues.

261
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:31,500
And if you really want
to start assigning blame,

262
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:33,330
he wasn't even an employee.

263
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:34,900
He was fired.

264
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:37,330
He used my ID to get in the front gate.

265
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:38,770
I gave it to him.

