00:10:38,810 --> 00:10:40,070
If you wanted to,

267
00:10:40,110 --> 00:10:43,830
you could argue that the
whole thing was my fault.

268
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,800
Guy brings a gun to work,kills
himself and two others.

269
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:47,800
My fault.

270
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:48,970
Three guns.

271
00:10:49,010 --> 00:10:50,670
Excuse me?

272
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:52,970
<i>He came to the office with three guns.</i>

273
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:55,170
Right.

274
00:10:55,210 --> 00:10:57,630
Aerodytech is a government contractor.

275
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,970
The sensitive nature of their work means

276
00:11:00,010 --> 00:11:02,500
that they're a target for terrorists,

277
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:04,900
disgruntled employees,and competitors.

278
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:07,370
And you're telling me you think
it's okay that the only thing

279
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:11,700
standing between Aerodytech
and Bruce Rossiter's guns

280
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:14,370
was your ID at an
unmanned security gate?

281
00:11:14,410 --> 00:11:17,370
Mr. Dubois,these people

282
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:20,230
did not take adequate precautions

283
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:24,000
to protect the country,its
secrets,or their employees.

284
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:26,100
Stop working so hard to defend them.

285
00:11:26,140 --> 00:11:28,130
They certainly didn't
do much to defend you.

286
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:35,500
It's me,the hunter-gatherer.

287
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:37,330
I bring food

288
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:40,300
and communications
from the outside world.

289
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:42,000
In here.

290
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:46,200
Daddy's home.

291
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:49,300
Can I steal you for a minute?

292
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:52,530
Bridge,would you finish
setting the table for Mommy?

293
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:54,400
I can't decide if this guy's our savior

294
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,870
or Mephistopheles in lawyer's clothing.

295
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:58,770
There's something about his intensity.

296
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:01,100
On the one hand,I love the fact

297
00:12:01,140 --> 00:12:02,470
that he might be working for us,

298
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:04,030
and on the other hand,I
feel ashamed of myself

299
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:07,270
for hiring somebody like
that to do our bidding.

300
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,170
Why are you smiling? What
are you smiling about?

301
00:12:12,610 --> 00:12:14,900
You're talking to me. I miss that.

302
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:22,230
I honestly just don't know what to do.

303
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:24,930
I like Aerodytech.

304
00:12:24,980 --> 00:12:27,430
And it just seems wrong when I...

305
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,500
when I think about my dead friends,

306
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:31,100
and I think about that awful day,

307
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:33,830
to be thinking about money.

308
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:37,600
Maybe that's naive.

309
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:39,700
I mean,what would I say to Mr. Canty?

310
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:41,600
Oh,my God,he called you.

311
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,300
Left you a message on
the answering machine.

312
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:45,430
I didn't get a chance to tell you.

313
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,330
He wants to have lunch
with you tomorrow.

314
00:12:47,380 --> 00:12:50,370
See,I already feel like I'm cheating
on him by having this conversation.

315
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:54,400
He said "millions of dollars. "

316
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:58,030
Maybe "tens of millions of dollars. "

317
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:02,370
All right,ladies and
gentlemen,five women are dead now,

318
00:13:02,410 --> 00:13:06,730
all brutally murdered
by the same sociopath.

319
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:08,970
Are you embarrassed?

320
00:13:09,010 --> 00:13:10,870
Are you ashamed?

321
00:13:10,910 --> 00:13:13,600
I know I am.

322
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:18,230
Our local hotels and restaurants
are losing millions in revenue.

323
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:20,130
Our convention center is empty.

324
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:22,730
Every day brings a new cancellation.

325
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:25,000
And our Chamber of
Commerce is telling me

326
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:28,230
that it will take years
to shake off the perception

327
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:30,770
of Phoenix as an unsafe city to visit.

328
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:36,070
Well,I won'have it.

329
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:38,100
Not on my watch.

330
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:45,240
I'm not going down like my predecessor.

331
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:50,060
I like being the new DA of Phoenix.

332
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:52,660
Huh?

333
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:04,900
There's another murder after Debra's.

334
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:06,250
Huh?

335
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:09,380
I said,"There's another
murder after Debra's. "

336
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:13,110
I'm sorry. I know that
you said something to me

337
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,640
'cause I saw your mouth was moving.

338
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,270
It was awful.

339
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:18,280
Five women killed.

340
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:19,570
Debra and then another one,

341
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:21,460
and Devalos wasn't the DA anymore.

342
00:14:21,470 --> 00:14:22,690
They got rid of him.

343
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:24,930
Okay,okay.

344
00:14:24,970 --> 00:14:26,630
So this is in the future?

345
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:29,660
Yeah. But you don't
know specifically when?

346
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,660
What can I do that I
haven't already done?

347
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,910
I tried to convince
Debra she was in danger.

348
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:36,540
She wouldn't believe me.

349
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:38,530
What am I going to do? Tell my boss,

350
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:40,210
"Hey,now might be a great time

351
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:42,320
"for you to get that resume out there.

352
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:44,860
Check out the DA wanted ads"?

353
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:47,530
What,laughing,sleepy boy?

354
00:14:47,570 --> 00:14:49,390
You going to make some more fun of me?

355
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:51,160
No,I'm not making fun of you.

356
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:54,460
I just seems to me like
this is just a math problem.

357
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,860
What's a math problem?

358
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:59,390
You said there are five victims

359
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,390
and that your friend
is the fourth victim.

360
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,960
And you implied that Devalos gets fired

361
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,260
after the death of the fifth girl.

362
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:10,230
So it just seems pretty obvious
to me what you've got to do.

363
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:12,730
Okay.

364
00:15:12,770 --> 00:15:15,260
Well,just don't let
your friend get murdered.

365
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:16,830
Then your friend lives;

366
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:19,260
Devalos doesn't get fired;

367
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:20,930
there is no fifth victim;

368
00:15:20,970 --> 00:15:23,790
everyone lives happily...

369
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:27,230
well,I suppose the third
victim is not that happy,but...

370
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:29,730
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

371
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:31,890
All right,I'm not making myself clear.

372
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:36,090
Okay,if your friend
is the fourth victim,

373
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:37,930
then just don't let her be.

374
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:39,290
Put her under surveillance.

375
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:40,890
Don't let her out of your sight.

376
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,790
You know this guy is going
to come and look for her,

377
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,230
so just be there when he does.

378
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:47,690
Stop the murder,stop the murderer.

379
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,530
I need you to do something for me.

380
00:15:56,570 --> 00:15:58,530
Joe? Hey,Marcus.

381
00:15:58,570 --> 00:16:00,260
How are you? Texting my wife.

382
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:02,190
New phone,does everything
but make coffee.

383
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:04,230
That's nice.

384
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:08,090
You're looking good. Relaxed.

385
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:10,690
I talked to Dr. Myers.

386
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:12,890
He's very pleased about everything.

387
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:17,430
Joe,we miss you.

388
00:16:17,470 --> 00:16:18,830
Hey,I miss being there.

389
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:21,060
I don't know what happened
that week I came back...

390
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,530
Doesn't matter. Myers
says you're better.

391
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:25,330
So if you're willing,

392
00:16:25,370 --> 00:16:27,790
you and your,uh,new phone...

393
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:30,360
More than willing.

394
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:33,090
Um...

395
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,790
What's this?

396
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,590
It's your annual bonus check.

397
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,960
Postdated,you won't be able

398
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,660
to cash it for a few weeks,but
we wanted you to have it.

399
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,630
So you know what we were thinking.

400
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:46,990
It's a little
premature,isn't it? It's May.

401
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,290
Well,given everything that's happened...

402
00:16:52,470 --> 00:16:54,530
I know.

403
00:16:54,570 --> 00:16:57,130
It's probably four times
what you were expecting.

404
00:16:57,170 --> 00:16:58,730
Closer to five.

405
00:16:58,770 --> 00:17:01,530
You know,I can hear you're in a hurry

406
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:03,690
to get back to work,but the truth is,

407
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:05,890
if you wanted a couple more weeks-

408
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:08,360
no doctors,no anything-

409
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,190
just a real vacation,

410
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:11,990
we would certainly understand.

411
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:18,260
Everything all right?

412
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:19,730
I won't lie to you.

413
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:23,090
You go through an
experience like this...

414
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:28,730
...and you start looking
at all your options.

415
00:17:28,770 --> 00:17:30,960
Looking back on your
whole professional life

416
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,230
wondering if it was
really as meaningful...

417
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:37,830
as you remember it being.

418
00:17:37,870 --> 00:17:40,660
Wondering if the people that
you've given your life to...

419
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:45,830
...well,if any of it
actually matters to them.

420
00:17:45,870 --> 00:17:48,330
Well,I hope you can see that it did...

421
00:17:48,370 --> 00:17:50,030
that it does.

422
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,530
You just need to take your time.

423
00:17:52,570 --> 00:17:53,960
Make sure you're ready.

424
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,330
Then come back and we'll
hit the ground running.

425
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:00,230
Thank you.

426
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:04,930
To the future.

427
00:18:08,370 --> 00:18:10,230
Oh,actually,

428
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:13,030
there is one little
thing I need you to do

429
00:18:13,070 --> 00:18:14,660
sooner rather than later.

430
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:18,690
Just over the weekend,take it home,

431
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:21,830
and when you get a chance,uh,read
it over and then sign it.

432
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:23,490
I'm sorry,Marcus. What is this?

433
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:26,930
Oh,it's just a standard form.

434
00:18:26,970 --> 00:18:29,560
The insurance company
wanted us to give it to you.

435
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:31,690
It's,uh,some kind

436
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:33,560
of liability waiver.

437
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,490
"I,Joseph Dubois,hereby
release Aerodytech,

438
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:38,490
"its officers and
shareholders from any claim,

439
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:40,060
"future or past,relating to events

440
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:43,230
occurring on or off
company property... "

441
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:48,160
You mind if I have an
attorney take a look at this?

442
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,860
Of course not.

443
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,060
It's a little awkward,but,uh...

444
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:55,860
I need to have that back
before you can return to work.

445
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,490
Excuse me?

446
00:18:57,540 --> 00:19:00,030
It's not us. It's the insurance company.

447
00:19:00,070 --> 00:19:02,290
They're insisting we get
your signature on those

448
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:04,190
before we can bring you back.

449
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,960
You understand.

450
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,030
Marcus,are you saying
that if I don't sign these,

451
00:19:08,070 --> 00:19:09,260
I can't come back to work?

452
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,890
No,I'm not saying that.

453
00:19:10,940 --> 00:19:12,390
They can't do that.

454
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,190
Aerodytech can't do that.

455
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,360
You can't fire someone without cause.

456
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,190
Joe,please don't go down this road.

457
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:21,930
There's always cause.
They'll find cause.

458
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:23,960
No! There is no cause.

459
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,760
What did I do?

460
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:29,860
I sat there for eight hours

461
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:32,260
with a gun pointed at me

462
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:34,730
and tried to reason with a man.

463
00:19:34,770 --> 00:19:37,060
That's cause?! That's not cause.

464
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,660
How about not showing up

465
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:41,460
for your company-mandated
therapy last week?

466
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,090
The insurance company
seems to think that's cause.

467
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:47,260
Wait a minute. Where are you going?

468
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,560
We haven't even ordered yet.

469
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,560
I'm not hungry.

470
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,560
I want you to think about this.

471
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,760
There's a lot of money in that envelope.

472
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,960
And who knows,maybe I
could get you a little more.

473
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,390
You...

474
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:01,160
<i>I'm telling you,I didn't
know what to think.</i>

475
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,490
It felt like an ultimatum.

476
00:20:03,540 --> 00:20:05,160
I came this close to calling that lawyer

477
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,930
and saying,"Let's go. "

478
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:10,430
Well,maybe Mr. Canty was being honest.

479
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:11,830
I'm sure their insurance company

480
00:20:11,870 --> 00:20:13,930
is terrified that you're going to sue.

481
00:20:13,970 --> 00:20:16,190
I'm sure they do want
them to get you to sign

482
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:18,460
some kind of waiver or something.

483
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,260
The good news is they're not
dropping you like a hot potato.

484
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:25,430
They're throwing money
at you to get you to stay.

485
00:20:25,470 --> 00:20:28,090
They just don't want you to
turn around a year from now

486
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:29,760
and drag them into court.

487
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,590
Well,it's not like
they're throwing millions,

488
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:34,590
certainly not tens of millions.

489
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,530
I don't know. Of course there's

490
00:20:36,570 --> 00:20:39,190
no guarantee that if I do sue...

491
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:42,890
Do me a favor. Dream about us tonight.

492
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:44,560
Tell me what I should do.

493
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,030
Well,that's not fair.

494
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:48,390
If I tell you what to do,who's
going to tell me what to do?

495
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:50,290
What are you talking about?
You don't need advice.

496
00:20:50,340 --> 00:20:52,460
You know everything before
it happens. Not true.

497
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,460
That little piece of advice
you gave me this morning?

498
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,860
Yeah,that worked out for you?

499
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,860
I went right to Scanlon,told
him he had to put Debra

500
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,630
under 24-hour surveillance.

501
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:02,660
That's my girl.

502
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:09,630
And I told him about some filthy,

503
00:21:09,670 --> 00:21:12,430
dirty text messages I got this morning.

504
00:21:12,470 --> 00:21:14,890
I'd like to have him
investigate to put a stop to it.

505
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:17,290
Oh,really? You want those to stop,huh?

506
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,990
Someone is feeling better.

507
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:25,290
What can I tell you?

508
00:21:25,340 --> 00:21:27,290
It's a triumph of the human spirit.

509
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:36,190
Sorry,ma'am.

510
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,730
I didn't realize you were
here. I'll come back later.

511
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,390
Ma'am,are you okay?

512
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:50,530
Ma'am?

513
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:04,720
A maid found her in the hotel bathtub.

514
00:22:05,540 --> 00:22:08,000
And we're sure it's this... Recapitator.

515
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:09,140
Not some copycat?

516
00:22:09,180 --> 00:22:11,940
The previous victim's
head was there as well.

517
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:15,100
I got here as quickly as I could.

518
00:22:15,150 --> 00:22:16,770
You okay?

519
00:22:16,810 --> 00:22:18,070
I'd rather be at the scene.

520
00:22:18,110 --> 00:22:19,500
I'd rather not be looking at pictures.

521
00:22:19,550 --> 00:22:21,770
But when the mayor asks
you to sit this one out...

522
00:22:21,810 --> 00:22:23,900
When the governor asks
you to sit this one out...

523
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:25,900
Press is getting pretty vicious.

524
00:22:25,950 --> 00:22:27,240
Care to see the carnage?

525
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,340
That's okay.

526
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:29,400
I've seen it.

527
00:22:29,450 --> 00:22:30,500
So,who was she?

528
00:22:30,550 --> 00:22:32,740
